org.dmd.util.parsing
Class ConfigLocation

java.lang.Object
  org.dmd.util.parsing.ConfigLocation

public class ConfigLocation
extends java.lang.Object

The ConfigLocation simply indicates the name of a config file (a file with a .dms suffix) and its location on the file system.

getFileName

public java.lang.String getFileName()
The complete file name of this config file OR When the file is found in a JAR file, it's the URL of the file, for example
"jar:file:" + jarFileName + "!/" + jarDirectory + "/" + configName + ".xxx"
URL url = new URL(fileName);

Returns:
The file name.

getConfigParentDirectory

public java.lang.String getConfigParentDirectory()

getVersion

public java.lang.String getVersion()
Returns:
The version of the config in numeric form i.e. if your config was in a folder called v3dot5 the version will be "3.5". If the config file wasn't in a version directory, this will be null.

getJarDirectory

public java.lang.String getJarDirectory()
If the schema was in a JAR, this is the name of the directory within the JAR where it was found.

Returns:
The directory path segment - the file separators in this are forward slashes.
